Letʻs measure frogs!

If you are interested in measuring morphometrics on frogs, I hope you find this project website helpful. We are collecting morphometric data on microhylid frogs from the Papuan region (subfamily Asterophryinae) using calipers.

Getting started

Please look over the definition of the measurements and Landmarks and assessing Repeatability. Assessing repeatability is important for morphometric analyses in general and absolutely critical when multiple investigators are taking measurements.
